# =============================================================================
# Recommended .dockerignore for the IMPERIUM Docker builds (server + client).
#
# This file lives in deploy/ because the repo ROOT is owned by the scaffold
# team: copy it to the repo root as `.dockerignore` when adopting — Docker only
# reads it from the root of the build context (which is the repo root for both
# deploy/Dockerfile.server and deploy/Dockerfile.client).
# TODO(scaffold): adopt by copying deploy/dockerignore to the repo root as .dockerignore (root is owned by the scaffold team).
#
# NOTE: do NOT add a bare `deploy` exclusion here — Dockerfile.client COPYs
# deploy/nginx.conf from the build context.
# =============================================================================

# VCS / CI
.git
.github

# Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image)
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build output (rebuilt inside the image)
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
coverage
**/coverage

# Non-code workstreams — never needed in server/client images
audio
art
docs
sim
lore

# Environment files — never bake secrets/local config into images
.env
.env.*

# Docs — no markdown is needed at build or run time
*.md
**/*.md

# Editor / OS noise
.vscode
.idea
*.log
.DS_Store
